Class AbstractFunctionalOperationTypeImplementation<FinalType>

  • Type Parameters:
    FinalType - The final type extending this class.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    OperationTypeImplementation<FinalType>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Activation, Broadcast, Convolution, GenericImplementation, Operator, Scalarization
    public abstract class AbstractFunctionalOperationTypeImplementation<FinalType>
extends AbstractBaseOperationTypeImplementation<FinalType>
    This is the base class for implementations of the OperationTypeImplementation interface. The class implements the component logic required by said interface. Additionally it contains useful methods used to process passed arguments of execution calls. Conceptually this class represents "a way of execution" for the OperationType to which an instance of this class would belong. The "+" operator for example has different OperationTypeImplementation instances for different ExecutionCall instances. Tensors within an execution call having the same shape would trigger the Operation instance of the OperationType, whereas otherwise the Convolution or Broadcast implementation might be called.
